==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Malacosteon
<hw>Mal`a*cos"te*on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., Gr. fr.
<grk>malako`s</grk> soft + <grk>'oste`on</grk> bone.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A peculiar disease of the bones, in consequence
of which they become softened and capable of being bent without
breaking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malacostomous</ent>⟦br⟧
